gomodel:SYNGO_1052  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 is a synaptic guanine nucleotide exchange factor present in inhibitory postsynapses with the capability to activate Arf6. IQSEC3 interacts with gephrin at inhibitory synapses (Fig. 1, 2, 4) and overexpression and knock-down experiments in cultured neurons indicate that IQSEC3 is involved in the regulation of synapse development and this activity is dependent on the Arf-GEF activity of IQSEC3 (Fig. 5, 8,).\n\nThe referenced paper demonstrates that IQSEC3 activates Arf6 and localizes to inhibitory synapses.\n\n5/7/2017 Pim\n- SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 over-expression is shown to affect the number of DIV10 neuron synapses (Fig.5). Interaction of SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 with the postsynaptic marker protein Gephyrin is needed for this effect (Fig.7). This effect does rely on the ArfGEF activity of SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 (Fig.8). Fig.10 shows effect shRNA SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 KD on postsynaptic specialization size. Together this can be used to justify the term:\n\n\"positive regulation of ARF protein signal transduction (GO:0032014)\"\noccurs_in \"postsynapse (GO:0098794)\"\npart_of \"postsynapse organization (GO:0050808)\"\n\n29/5/2018 Pim\n- Because SynArfGEF/BRAG3/IQSEC3 interacts with gephyrin and is essential in the postsynaptic recruitment of this protein I have annotated to the more specific term 'postsynapse organization (GO:0099173)' instead of 'synapse organization (GO:0050808)'.. Experimental description: Expression plasmids for fragments of rat IQSEC3 (GenBankTM accession number, NM_207617) were prepared by amplifying..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1052" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

